# Backups Directory

This directory contains database backup files created by `scripts/db-backup.sh`.

## Important Notes

- ‚úÖ This directory is version-controlled (.gitkeep ensures it exists)
- ‚ùå Individual backup files (.sql.gz) are NOT committed (see .gitignore)
- üì¶ Backup files are managed automatically (max 30 files retained)
- üîÑ New backups can be created on-demand via: `./scripts/db-backup.sh`

## Files Here

```
backup_20240202_103045.sql.gz    # Timestamped database dumps
backup_20240201_000000.sql.gz    # Compressed format (~50MB each)
test-restore_*.log               # Restore test results
```

## Usage

**Create Manual Backup:**
```bash
export SUPABASE_DB_URL="postgresql://..."
./scripts/db-backup.sh
```

**Test Restore:**
```bash
export SUPABASE_TEST_DB_URL="postgresql://..."
./scripts/test-backup-restore.sh
```

## Configuration

- **Retention**: Last 30 backup files
- **Format**: SQL (gzip compressed)
- **Size**: ~40-60 MB per backup
- **Frequency**: On-demand (or weekly via CI/CD)

See `supabase/docs/BACKUPS.md` for full documentation.
